<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1917-05-29T17:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1917-05-29T17:00:00-05:00" n="720" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d720">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 701.67m51</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to
                                the Ambassador in France</hi> (<persName corresp="#p_SWG1" type="to"><hi rend="italic">Sharp</hi></persName>)</head>
                        <opener>
                            <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram]</seg>
                        </opener>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1917-05-29T17:00:00-05:00">
                                    <hi rend="italic">May 29, 1917, 5 p.m.</hi>
                                </date>
                            </dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>2294. Investigate fully and report promptly status of Armenian
                            representative accredited to France. What status does this
                            representative claim, what does he state to be the purpose of his
                            mission, and how is he received by French Government?</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <persName corresp="#p_LR1">
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Lansing</hi>
                                </persName>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>